                            </button>
                            <div class="faq-content">
                                <p>Yes, every registry modification has a built-in reverse action. You can toggle any setting off and click "Apply Changes", or use the "Restore Registry Backups" tool to revert all states.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
                                <span>Does this work on both Windows 10 and Windows 11?</span>
                                <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                                    <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
                                </svg>
                            </button>
                            <div class="faq-content">
                                <p>Yes, ApexDebloater supports 64-bit editions of both Windows 10 and Windows 11. It dynamically detects your operating system version and only displays safe, applicable registry keys for your environment.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
                                <span>Will it break Windows Update or system security?</span>
                                <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                                    <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
                                </svg>
                            </button>
                            <div class="faq-content">
                                <p>No, none of the "Safe" tweaks interfere with Windows Update or critical patch delivery. The tool specifically focuses on removing advertising, user-tracking telemetry, and pre-installed OEM apps.</p>
